# Project Rules

<!--
  Fill this in for your project. This article is where you describe WHAT the
  swarm should build and any project-specific rules. Everything in angle
  brackets is a placeholder to replace.
-->

## Project Shape
- SwarmForge coding project with two agents: coder and cleaner.
- The coder is the master worktree role; the cleaner works in its own worktree
  in batch mode.
- Project language: <FILL IN, e.g. Python, Go, TypeScript>. Use that language's
  standard unit-test runner and local verification.

## Task
- <Describe the behavior you want built. The coder implements it with TDD in
  small slices, committing and handing off to the cleaner after each slice.
  Prefer starting with one small slice and letting the coder -> cleaner cycle
  run before adding more.>

## Tooling Note
- If a tool named in a role prompt (coverage, CRAP, DRY, mutation) is not
  installed, note it in one line and skip it rather than installing anything.

## Local Configuration
- Keep swarm state under `.swarmforge/` and worktrees under `.worktrees/`.

## Handoffs
- Prefer terse, explicit handoffs that report state and request role-appropriate
  review. Do not include sender process narrative.

## Ownership
- Do not change another role's prompt or workflow ownership without explicit
  user direction.
